                <p>
                    <app loc="1"><lem>Ἀριστοτέλε<unclear>υ</unclear>ς</lem>
                        <rdg resp="#cassels1955 #dthorn-thorn2009">Ἀριστοτέλευς</rdg>
                        <rdg resp="#robinson1913">Ἀριστοτέλεις <note>for <foreign xml:lang="grc">Ἀριστοτέλης</foreign></note></rdg>
                        
                    </app>
               </p>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Tombe</supplied> d'Aristotélès.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Tomb</supplied> of Aristoteles.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Tomba</supplied> di Aristoteles.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>We have here, as in other funerary mentions on sarcophagi, the name of the deceased at the genitive: he is considered the owner of the sarcopaghus.</p>
